org.semanticweb.rulewerk.core.model.implementation

Class AbstractLiteralImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.semanticweb.rulewerk.core.model.implementation.AbstractLiteralImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Entity, Literal, SyntaxObject
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NegativeLiteralImpl, PositiveLiteralImpl

    public abstract class AbstractLiteralImpl
extends Object
implements Literal
    Implements Literal objects. A literal is a formula of the form +P(t1,...,tn) or -P(t1,...,tn) for P a Predicate name, and t1,...,tn some Terms. The number of terms corresponds to the Predicate arity.
    Author:
    david.carral@tu-dresden.de, Markus Kr√∂tzsch
